Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with morphological inflection generation. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes improvements to neural methods for low-resource settings. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with machine learning techniques for natural language processing. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper proposes a novel attention architecture for the inflection decoder. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is another possible category as the paper deals with neural methods and their improvements.
